Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_pg_cover_cell(25.10)                        create_pg_cover_cell(25.10)

Name
       create_pg_cover_cell  -  Creates a routed PG cover cell and generates a
       LEF files for it

Syntax
       create_pg_cover_cell

        [-help]

       -box {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}

       -cell <cell_name>

       -lef_file <file_name>

       -routing_layers <layer_name>

       Creates a routed PG cover cell and generates a LEF files for it.

       Note:

              *

                The create_pg_cover_cell command can only be used  for  inter-
                poser designs with PG routing, excluding signal nets.

              *

                R0 is the default orientation.

              *

                Before  using  the  create_pg_cover_cell command you must save
                the design database using the saveDesign command. This is done
                to ensure that the database at the creation of  the  PG  cover
                cell  (create_pg_cover_cell)  is  similar  to  the database to
                which   the   PG    cover    cell    instances    are    added
                (add_pg_cover_cell).

              * In order to make the PG cover cell dimensions exactly the same
                as  the  specified  box, you must set the constraints snapping
                rule to manufacturing grid:

                setFPlanMode -snapConstraintGrid manufacturing

Parameters
       -box {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies the coordinates of the box (<x1 y1 x2 y2>) for  creat-
              ing PG cover cell.

              Data_type: box, required

       -cell <cell_name>
              Specifies the name of the PG cover cell.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each create_pg_cover_cell  parameter.  For  a  de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man create_pg_cover_cell

       -lef_file <file_name>
              Specifies  the name of the LEF file that saves the PG cover cell
              information. The CLASS of the cell is COVER.

              Data_type: string, required

       -routing_layers <layer_name>
              Specifies the layers will be reserved for PG  routing  including
              the cut layers.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
              *

                The  following command creates a PG cover cell and generates a
                LEF file:

                create_pg_cover_cell -cell AA -box {0 0 250 250} -routing_lay-
                ers M3 -lef_file AALef

Related Information
              * add_pg_cover_cell

              * setFPlanMode

              * "Duplicating the PG Routing Pattern" in the Innovus User Guide

